added.title: Berserkers
added.description: The Cats' Lair is attacked by gold-loving robot pirates, the Berserkers! This is a good thing, really, since it means Lion-O and the ThunderKittens can ditch their chores and fight robo-pirates instead! Just don't tell Tygra!!!!

added.title: Jaga History
added.description: Freed from the Astral Plane, Jaga, ghost of the ThunderCats mentor, is now free to visit the Cats' Lair. Which means he can finally tell them why Thundera, their home world, exploded. It's story time!

added.title: Barbastella
added.description: While flying with his new invention, Panthro hits it off with a new friend, Barbastella, the Queen of the Bats! Now Panthro needs help getting ready for his big date with her, because it turns out Panthro is terrified of bats! Lion-O and Cheetara are happy to help but, wow, that is a lot to unpack.

added.title: Adopt a Jackal
added.description: After a battle with the Mutants, Jackalman gets confused and accidentally returns to the Cats' Lair with the Thundercats, he is the dumbest mutant. Jackalman pretends to be a Thundercat so his enemies won't catch him and the Thundercats pretend to play along because they feel bad for him!

added.title: Student Becomes the Teacher
added.description: Chef is knocked unconscious right before a School Board Evaluator shows up for a big review. Now Owen has to fill in so Chef doesn't lose his Teaching License and to ensure the kids earn the pony ride Chef promised for good behavior.

added.title: Pudding the Planet First
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Supply Mom
added.description: When Chef's mom becomes the supply teacher for a day Duncan replaces Chef's to-do list with one of his own.

added.title: Mooshy Mon Mons
added.description: After eating Chef's extremely rare and expensive chocolates Courtney drags Owen, Izzy and Beth all the way to the Norberian Alps of Fruffenberg to replace them.

added.title: #BreakingNews
added.description: Lois Lane's attempt to get an internship at the Daily Planet leads to her trying to unmask the Super Hero Girls, which forces the girls to a battle of wits with their greatest nemesis yet.

added.title: #EmperorPenguin
added.description: When Barbara Gordon attempts to do something nice for a friend, she ends up in the clutches of the Penguin, a high school mob boss who blackmails her into an increasingly desperate situation from which only Batgirl can save her.

added.title: #CrashCourse
added.description: When a high-speed chase breaks out during her driver's test, Diana Prince's desire to fight evil clashes with her desire to undergo a World of Man teenage rite of passage, getting her license.

added.title: #HousePest
added.description: When the Super Hero Girls discover that Diana doesn't actually have a home, they gladly open theirs up to her… until they discover that life with an Amazon is much more challenging than they expected.

added.title: The End of the Universe I Part 1
added.description: Starscream's fate at the hands of the Quintessons is revealed as he returns a three-headed Judge!

added.title: The End of the Universe I Part 2
added.description: Judge Starscream interrogates his Cybetronian prisoners while Optimus, Bee, and Wheeljack try to get back through the Multiverse Bridge.

added.title: The End of the Universe II Part 1
added.description: Windblade battles the Sharkticons to regain entry into Iaconus.

added.title: The End of the Universe II Part 2
added.description: While the Autobots and Decepticons stall Judge Starscream, Windblade tries to awaken Iaconus.

added.title: The End of the Universe III Part 1
added.description: Windblade wakes the War Titan Iaconus, only to discover the Quintessons have a Titan of their own!

added.title: The End of the Universe III Part 2
added.description: Iaconus and Croaton do battle as Optimus, Bumblebee and Wheeljack contend with the Scientist.

added.title: The End of the Universe IV Part 1
added.description: With Iaconus down, the Cybertronians make a desperate last stand against Judge Starscream.

added.title: The End of the Universe IV Part 2
added.description: Megatron returns from the Multiverse with enough new found powers to contest Judge Starscream, Windblade uses all her power attempting to free Croaton from Quintesson control.

removed.title: Bakuzoned!/The Golden Secret
removed.description: Bakuzoned!: Strata's return is much more than a simple rematch when he's been infected by a strange ooze and the AO are in danger of the same fate./The Golden Secret: Using Strata's gauntlet, the AO think they've found a way through the labyrinth, but soon discover trusting the enemy is not always best.

removed.title: Two Sides of the Coin/The Race for Gold
removed.description: Two Sides of the Coin: The AO and Magnus take parallel tracks to retrieve the same piece of data, one that promises a breakthrough in the Bakugan phenomenon./The Race for Gold: When the AO seek out a mythical, lost Bakugan, they get more than they bargained for when Magnus is on the trail of this new discovery, too.

removed.title: Girl Power/Return to the Fold
removed.description: Girl Power: When Lia battles with China Riot, they eventually come to an understanding as China finally realizes she's been set up by Benton/Tiko./Return to the Fold: On the run and with options dwindling, the AO turn to Shun's father, Ichiro Kazami, for help.

removed.title: The Golden Forge/A Deep Hibernation
removed.description: The Golden Forge: As Dan and Drago battle to free Trhyno from Tiko's infection, they learn the history of Vestroia and the nature of Golden Bakugan./A Deep Hibernation: Trhyno must give Dan and Drago the power they need if they are to have any chance in stopping Tiko from destroying both Vestroia and Earth.

removed.title: In the Wild/Call Me Old Brakken
removed.description: In the Wild: The AO are invited to a video-stars conference, but when the chartered jet goes down, the AO must give over to their wild sides to survive!/Call Me Old Brakken: Lord Brakken is the ultimate AO super-fan, but his zeal takes a dark turn when he looks to prove that he is their superior in battle.

removed.title: The Forbidden Isle/New World Orders
removed.description: The Forbidden Isle: The AO travel to a remote island in search of a Core Cell, but instead they find the Bakugan known as Kelion, which soon bonds with Dan./New World Orders: The AO discover a small group of kids and Bakugan being used as laborers against their will, but freeing them is only half the problem.

removed.title: Calling All Parents/Nowhere to Turn
removed.description: Calling All Parents: When the parents of the world are turned against their children and confiscate their Bakugan, the AO must seek out the Rowdy Reds./Nowhere to Turn: While the AO attempt to gain allies and warn other children, Wynton is confronted by Armstrong Tripp, who now works for Benton Dusk.

removed.title: The Healing Challenge/The Golden Drome
removed.description: The Healing Challenge: As the AO struggle to hold together, a discovery is made involving the Golden Bakugan, a Golden Drome, and curing of a Bakuzoned Gorthion./The Golden Drome: While Dan and Drago enter the Golden Drome to heal Trhyno, the rest of the AO defend the Golden Drome from a militia of human hunters.

removed.title: A Devil on Your Shoulder/Vestral Visions
removed.description: A Devil on Your Shoulder: Near giving up, Magnus gains new strength and insight on the AO's mission to find Core Cells that will eventually lead him down a dark hole./Vestral Visions: Drago's sickness leads Dan to a revelation that there is an ailing Core Cell and if they can't find a cure, the planet itself may falter.

removed.title: A Door Closes, A Door Opens/Kazami's Gambit
removed.description: A Door Closes, A Door Opens: Shun must stand up to his father, expose his cousin and protect his friends before Masato destroys everyone on Ichiro's island!/Kazami's Gambit: When Magnus looks to steal the Dimensional Doorway, Shun and Ichiro must make peace while the AO stop the Doorway from destroying them all.

removed.title: Our Ugly Selves/Trhyno Lives!
removed.description: Our Ugly Selves: Abandoned in the Vestroia Labyrinth, the AO must deal with their personal losses and, worse, the Bakuzoned Awful Ones!/Trhyno Lives!: When the AO and Magnus form an alliance to free the Golden Bakugan, their differences lead to a horrible sacrifice for Dan and Lia.

removed.title: In My Room/An Army of Their Own
removed.description: In My Room: When the AO report that they've been fighting the wrong fight, they discover that Benton has been corrupted by the villainous Tiko./An Army of Their Own: The AO are forced to turn to Philomena Dusk for help, only to realize that they have led Benton/Tiko right to the AAAnimus Campus.

removed.title: The Mask of Pride/The Graveyard of Courage
removed.description: The Mask of Pride: Driven by revenge, Magnus decides to go back into the labyrinth, face the AO and claim the Fortus Core Cell energy for himself./The Graveyard of Courage: Super charged by the Fortus Core Cell, Magnus wages war on the AO only to discover his newfound power has a price attached.

removed.title: Seek and Hide/Family First
removed.description: Seek and Hide: Sent to investigate a Japanese island by Benton Dusk, the AO discover a hidden facility conducting experiments that affect The Hide./Family First: Trapped by his father, Shun is forced to battle his own friends, revealing dark secrets about the Kazami family and Masato's experiments.

removed.title: Kazami Family Feud/Greatest of the Kazami
removed.description: Kazami Family Feud: Masato attacks, but the AO soon realize that Ichiro is keeping a Golden Bakugan captive, forcing them to choose between the lesser of two evils!/Greatest of the Kazami: Shun makes an impassioned plea to Ichiro, but it is too late as the Kazami compound is overrun by Bakuzon and the Visvus Cell is lost.

removed.title: Planet-Ception/United We Stand
removed.description: Planet-Ception: The final showdown between Tiko and AO with the future of Earth and Vestroia in balance./United We Stand: The Awesome Ones return home as heroes, wondering what battles await them in the future.

removed.title: Hide Matrix and Seek/Or Forever Hold Your Peace
removed.description: Hide Matrix and Seek: The AO go undercover to try and pass as citizens of Lord Brakken, but quickly discover that even minor celebrity makes anonymity impossible./Or Forever Hold Your Peace: The AO seek to rescue Lia from an arranged marriage with Lord Brakken only to discover she just made a major discovery for the Bakugan!

removed.title: Stormy Weather/Who Can It Be Now
removed.description: Stormy Weather: On a flight to their next Core Cell mission, the AO's plane falls under attack by Pyravian, who strangely believes the team to be Bakuzon./Who Can It Be Now: The AO find themselves in a battle against the Bakuzon forces of Tiko that upends everything they thought they knew about Core Cells.

removed.title: Happy/One Way or Another
removed.description: Happy: The AO expect a fight in Brakistan, but soon discover that old enemies Lord Brakken, Magnus, and Nillious are unnaturally happy to see them./One Way or Another: In the heat of emotions, Shun convinces Lord Brakken that his usual enemies are the best allies he has to sequester a renegade Core Cell.

removed.title: Too Much/Who Are You?
removed.description: Too Much: The Hide Matrix goes crazy and a simple AO training mission turns into a complicated rampage that brings down Studio D./Who Are You?: After the loss of their HQ, the AO is a little off, but in talking to Benton Dusk, they learn a new sense of purpose for their team.

removed.title: At the Beginning, an Ending/This Late Hour
removed.description: At the Beginning, an Ending: When Shun and Lia track down Ichiro and Masato on their quest for more allies, they are forced to battle a Bakuzoned Ichiro!/This Late Hour: Shun, Lia and Masato must square off against the Dusk Forces, but they are not alone when they are joined by Lt. Brenan and Kino.

removed.title: Bakuzon at the Gates
removed.description: Bakuzon at the Gates, Part 1: As the Dusk Forces storm the Numena Core Cell, infighting between the Awesome Ones and their allies threatens to tear them all apart./Bakuzon at the Gates, Part 2: Tiko/Dusk Forces have coalesced into global power and are waging a no holds barred assault on the Numena Core Cell.

removed.title: The Bakugan Breakers/The Awful Ones
removed.description: The Bakugan Breakers: Magnus's new team of Bakugan Brawlers overhear Lightning's warnings of a sick Core Cell and decide to capture the dog to find its location./The Awful Ones: Magnus heads into the Labyrinth to claim the Fortus Core Cell for his own, but comes in direct contact with the evil versions of the AO.

removed.title: Vestroia
removed.description: Vestroia, Part 1: The AO discover the only way to stop Magnus, and possibly save him, involves shutting down the infected Fortus Core Cell./Vestroia, Part 2: The AO must decide whether or not to help Benton Dusk destroy the infected Fortus Core Cell, risking the destruction of their own Bakugan.
